---

### Updated Script Without &quot;Grandma&quot;

```bash
#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash

# Folder where your files are
cd ~/storage/shared/Android

# Output files
LITERAL_OUTFILE=&quot;literal_mentions_log.txt&quot;
SYMBOLIC_OUTFILE=&quot;symbolic_mentions_log.txt&quot;

echo &quot;Literal Mentions Log - $(date)&quot; &gt; &quot;$LITERAL_OUTFILE&quot;
echo &quot;----------------------------------&quot; &gt;&gt; &quot;$LITERAL_OUTFILE&quot;

echo &quot;Symbolic Mentions Log - $(date)&quot; &gt; &quot;$SYMBOLIC_OUTFILE&quot;
echo &quot;-----------------------------------&quot; &gt;&gt; &quot;$SYMBOLIC_OUTFILE&quot;

# Define literal and symbolic keywords (without &quot;grandma&quot;)
literal_keywords=(&quot;granny&quot; &quot;nana&quot; &quot;grandmother&quot;)
symbolic_keywords=(&quot;family&quot; &quot;heritage&quot; &quot;tradition&quot; &quot;wisdom&quot; &quot;generations&quot; &quot;legacy&quot; &quot;memories&quot;)

# Function to search and log
search_and_log() {
    local keywords=(&quot;$@&quot;)
    local output_file=&quot;$1&quot; # Will be overwritten by literal or symbolic log

    for keyword in &quot;${keywords[@]:1}&quot;; do
        find . -type f -name &quot;*.dat&quot; | while read -r file; do
            echo &quot;Checking $file...&quot;
            grep -in &quot;$keyword&quot; &quot;$file&quot; | while read -r line; do
                echo &quot;[$file] $line&quot; &gt;&gt; &quot;$output_file&quot;
            done
        done
    done
}

# Search for literal mentions
search_and_log &quot;$LITERAL_OUTFILE&quot; &quot;${literal_keywords[@]}&quot;

# Search for symbolic mentions
search_and_log &quot;$SYMBOLIC_OUTFILE&quot; &quot;${symbolic_keywords[@]}&quot;

echo &quot;Done. Results saved to $LITERAL_OUTFILE and $SYMBOLIC_OUTFILE&quot;
```

---

### Changes:
- **Removed &quot;grandma&quot;** from the literal keyword list.
- The script now searches for **&quot;granny,&quot; &quot;nana,&quot;** and **&quot;grandmother&quot;** in the literal category, while keeping the same symbolic keywords for broader concepts like **&quot;family,&quot; &quot;tradition,&quot; &quot;legacy,&quot;** etc.

